This Cisco CCNA Wireless video training series with Keith Baker covers the fundamentals, installation and troubleshooting of Wireless LANs (WLANs), including the integration of Access Points (APs), WLAN Controllers (WLCs) and implementation of WLAN security. This series presents everything you need to know for the 640-722 IUWNE (Implementing Cisco Unified Wireless Networking Essentials) exam.

Recommended skills:
Cisco CCENT/ICND1-level knowledge or equivalent. (CCENT/ICND1 certification is a prerequisite for the 640-722 exam)

Recommended equipment:
Wireless controller or ESX environment where you can run the virtual WLC (vWLC). Evaluation copies of the vWLC are available from Cisco.
At least one AP compatible with the vWLC or physical controller you will be using.

This series will assist you in obtaining the knowledge and skills to configure, implement, monitor, troubleshoot, and support Cisco WLANs.
